---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import RelatedTools from '../../../components/RelatedTools.astro';

// Tool metadata
const name = "401(k) & Retirement Savings Calculator";
const category = "finance";
const tier = "Finance & Tax";
const description =
  "Project your retirement savings balance and future income based on annual contributions, employer matches, and compound growth across multiple countries.";

// SEO-optimized metadata
const seoTitle = "401(k) Calculator & Retirement Savings Estimator";
const seoDescription =
  "Free 401(k) calculator with employer match. Project your retirement savings, plan to max out 401(k) contributions, model withdrawals, and compare your nest egg to average retirement savings by age.";
const seoKeywords =
  "401(k) calculator & retirement savings, 401(k) calculator, 401k calculator, 401k calculator with match, bankrate 401k calculator, solo 401k calculator, simple 401k calculator, 401k calculator simple, retirement 401k calculator, 401k calculator withdrawal, max out 401k calculator, early withdrawal 401k calculator, average retirement savings by age, retirement calculator, retirement calculator 401k";
const canonicalUrl = "https://toolkify.app/tools/finance/retirement-401k";
---

<Layout
  title={seoTitle}
  description={seoDescription}
  keywords={seoKeywords}
  canonical={canonicalUrl}
  ogType="website"
  toolName={name}
  toolCategory={category}
  hideBanner={true}
>
  <!-- SEO JSON-LD Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "401(k) Calculator & Retirement Savings Estimator",
      "url": "https://toolkify.app/tools/finance/retirement-401k",
      "description": "Free 401(k) calculator and retirement savings estimator. Project your 401k balance with employer match, plan to max out contributions, model early withdrawals, and benchmark against average retirement savings by age. Supports US 401(k), CA RRSP/TFSA, UK Pensions, AU Superannuation, and Indian EPF/NPS systems with interactive charts and growth schedules.",
      "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "All",
      "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript. Requires HTML5.",
      "keywords": "401(k) calculator & retirement savings, 401k calculator, 401k calculator with match, solo 401k calculator, simple 401k calculator, retirement 401k calculator, 401k calculator withdrawal, max out 401k calculator, early withdrawal 401k calculator, average retirement savings by age, retirement calculator",
      "featureList": [
        "401k calculator with employer match",
        "Max out 401k contribution planning with annual limits and age 50+ catch-up",
        "401k withdrawal and retirement income estimate using the 4% rule",
        "Average retirement savings by age benchmarking",
        "Real vs nominal inflation-adjusted balance projection",
        "Year-by-year growth schedule with CSV and Excel export",
        "Multi-country support: 401(k), RRSP/TFSA, Pension, Super, EPF/NPS"
      ],
      "offers": {
        "@type": "Offer",
        "price": "0.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD"
      }
    }
  </script>

  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How long will my 401k last calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A 401(k) longevity calculator projects how many years your retirement savings will last based on your starting balance, investment return rate, annual inflation, and monthly withdrawal amount. Following the popular 4% withdrawal rule, a $1,000,000 portfolio is historically expected to last 30 years or more, whereas higher withdrawal rates will deplete the nest egg much sooner.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much does 401k contribution reduce taxes?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Traditional 401(k) contributions are made with pre-tax income, which lowers your Adjusted Gross Income (AGI) dollar-for-dollar. For example, if you contribute $10,000 and fall in the 22% federal tax bracket, you reduce your current tax bill by approximately $2,200. State and local income taxes may bring even more immediate tax savings.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much will my 401k pay me per month calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Your monthly retirement payment is determined by your total savings and your safe withdrawal rate. Using the 4% rule, you withdraw 4% of your starting balance in the first year and adjust for inflation thereafter. For a $500,000 nest egg, this provides an estimated initial payment of $20,000 per year, or approximately $1,667 per month.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much should i contribute to my 401k calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A common recommendation is to contribute 10% to 15% of your gross annual salary to your 401(k). At a minimum, you should contribute enough to capture 100% of your employer's matching contribution, as this match represents a guaranteed, risk-free return on your investment.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much should i put in 401k calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Deciding how much to put in your 401(k) depends on your age, retirement goals, and budget. For 2024, the IRS allows employee contributions up to $23,000 (plus an extra $7,500 catch-up if you are age 50 or older). Maximizing your contributions early in your career allows compound interest to do the heavy lifting.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much will my 401k be worth calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The future value of your 401(k) depends on your current balance, annual contributions, employer matching, investment growth rate, and timeline. For example, starting with $10,000 and contributing $500 per month for 30 years at a 7% average annual return will yield an estimated future balance of over $600,000.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much should i have in my 401k calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Standard retirement benchmarks suggest aiming for 1x your annual salary saved by age 30, 3x by age 40, 6x by age 50, and 8x to 10x by age 67. If you are behind these averages, increasing your contribution rate by just 1% or 2% can significantly close the gap over time.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much to contribute to 401k calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Determine your ideal contribution by using a retirement savings calculator to project different contribution percentages (such as 6%, 10%, or 15%). Ensure you contribute at least the match limit to secure your employer's full matching contribution, and scale up as your income grows.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much can i withdraw from my 401k calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The amount you can safely withdraw annually is typically guided by the 4% rule of thumb, which is designed to prevent you from outliving your assets. You can calculate your annual safe withdrawal by multiplying your retirement balance by 4% (e.g., $40,000 per year from a $1,000,000 balance).</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How long will my retirement savings last calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>How long your retirement nest egg lasts depends on your asset allocation, rate of return, inflation, and rate of spending. A retirement longevity calculator tracks these variables year-by-year, showing that a balanced portfolio with a conservative withdrawal rate of 3% to 4% has a high probability of lasting 30 years or more.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much to save for retirement calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To calculate your total retirement savings goal, a common rule of thumb is the \"25x rule.\" Estimate your desired annual spending in retirement (often 70% to 80% of your current income) and multiply it by 25. For example, if you plan to spend $80,000 annually, you should aim to save $2,000,000.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How long will $2 million last in retirement?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A $2 million nest egg will last indefinitely if you withdraw at or below a safe rate of 3.5% to 4% (generating $70,000 to $80,000 annually, adjusted for inflation). If you withdraw a higher amount, such as $120,000 annually (6%), the funds may run out in 20 to 25 years depending on market performance.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>


  <section
    class="max-w-[1280px] w-full mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 py-6 flex flex-col gap-6 animate-fade-in-up pb-24 lg:pb-12"
  >    <!-- Breadcrumb & Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
      <nav
        class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold text-slate uppercase"
        aria-label="Breadcrumb"
      >
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Tools</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-blue capitalize">{category}</span>
      </nav>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between mt-0.5 gap-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <h1
            id="tool-title"
            class="font-display font-medium text-2xl sm:text-3xl tracking-tight text-primary"
          >
            {name}
          </h1>
          <span
            class="badge-tag-purple bg-surface-pricing-featured text-brand-blue text-[10px] py-0.5 px-2.5 rounded-full font-semibold uppercase shrink-0"
            >{tier}</span
          >
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <button
            type="button"
            id="share-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Share tool link"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.684 10.742l5.028-2.513m0 7.544l-5.028-2.513M18 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm-6 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 0a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
            </svg>
            <span>Share</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="how-it-works-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="How retirement calculator works"
          >
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              class="w-3.5 h-3.5"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            <span>How it works</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="reset-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-brand-red-dark hover:border-brand-red rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Reset calculator inputs"
          >
            <svg
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
              class="w-3.5 h-3.5"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2.5"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 1121.21 7.89M9 11l3-3 3 3m-3-3v12"
              ></path>
            </svg>
            <span>Reset</span>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Workspace Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
      <!-- Left Pane: Inputs (7 Columns) -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 flex flex-col gap-6">
        <div class="card-base flex flex-col gap-5">
          <h2
            class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-primary pb-2 border-b border-hairline flex items-center gap-2"
          >
            <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-brand-blue"></span>
            Personal & Contribution Details
          </h2>

          <!-- Warning Alert Box for Caps (hidden by default) -->
          <div
            id="contribution-warning"
            class="card-feature-rose !p-3 !rounded-lg text-[11px] flex flex-col gap-1 hidden"
          >
            <span class="font-bold text-coral-dark"
              >⚠️ Contribution Limit Warning:</span
            >
            <span id="warning-text" class="text-slate leading-relaxed">
              Your contribution exceeds the localized annual limit.
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- Age inputs -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <label
                for="current-age"
                class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal flex justify-between"
              >
                <span>Current Age</span>
                <span
                  id="current-age-val"
                  class="font-mono text-stone font-bold">25 yrs</span
                >
              </label>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <input
                  type="range"
                  id="current-age-range"
                  min="15"
                  max="80"
                  value="25"
                  class="w-full cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
                />
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="current-age"
                  value="25"
                  min="15"
                  max="80"
                  class="text-input w-20 text-center font-mono text-xs h-8 py-1"
                />
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <label
                for="retirement-age"
                class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal flex justify-between"
              >
                <span>Retirement Age</span>
                <span
                  id="retirement-age-val"
                  class="font-mono text-stone font-bold">65 yrs</span
                >
              </label>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <input
                  type="range"
                  id="retirement-age-range"
                  min="40"
                  max="90"
                  value="65"
                  class="w-full cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
                />
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="retirement-age"
                  value="65"
                  min="40"
                  max="90"
                  class="text-input w-20 text-center font-mono text-xs h-8 py-1"
                />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Age Presets -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
            <span
              class="text-[10px] font-semibold text-stone uppercase tracking-wider"
              >Quick Age Presets:</span
            >
            <div class="grid grid-cols-6 gap-1.5">
              {
                [55, 60, 62, 65, 67, 70].map((age) => (
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="preset-age-btn text-xs py-1.5 rounded-full font-semibold transition-all cursor-pointer border border-hairline text-slate bg-canvas hover:border-hairline-strong active:scale-95 flex items-center justify-center"
                    data-age={age}
                  >
                    {age}
                  </button>
                ))
              }
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Balance and Salary -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                <label
                  for="current-balance"
                  class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal"
                >
                  Current Retirement Balance
                </label>
                <select
                  id="currency-select"
                  class="text-[11px] font-semibold py-0.5 px-2 rounded-full border border-hairline bg-surface hover:bg-canvas cursor-pointer transition-all outline-none"
                  aria-label="Currency Select"
                >
                  <option value="USD" selected>$ USD</option>
                  <option value="CAD">$ CAD</option>
                  <option value="GBP">£ GBP</option>
                  <option value="AUD">$ AUD</option>
                  <option value="EUR">€ EUR</option>
                  <option value="INR">₹ INR</option>
                  <option value="Custom">Custom</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="relative">
                <span
                  class="absolute left-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-sm font-medium currency-symbol"
                  >$</span
                >
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="current-balance"
                  value="10000"
                  min="0"
                  step="1000"
                  class="text-input pl-7 font-mono text-sm w-full"
                />
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <label
                for="annual-salary"
                class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal"
              >
                Annual Salary
              </label>
              <div class="relative">
                <span
                  class="absolute left-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-sm font-medium currency-symbol"
                  >$</span
                >
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="annual-salary"
                  value="75000"
                  min="0"
                  step="1000"
                  class="text-input pl-7 font-mono text-sm w-full"
                />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Contribution rate -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
            <label
              for="your-contribution-rate"
              class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal flex justify-between"
            >
              <span>Your Contribution Rate</span>
              <span
                id="your-contribution-val"
                class="font-mono text-stone font-bold">8% ($6,000/yr)</span
              >
            </label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <input
                type="range"
                id="your-contribution-range"
                min="0"
                max="100"
                value="8"
                step="0.5"
                class="w-full cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
              />
              <div class="relative w-20 shrink-0">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="your-contribution-rate"
                  min="0"
                  max="100"
                  value="8"
                  step="0.1"
                  class="text-input pr-5 py-1 text-xs text-center font-mono h-8"
                />
                <span
                  class="absolute right-2 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-[10px]"
                  >%</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Employer Match rate & limit -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <label
                for="employer-match"
                class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal"
              >
                Employer Match Rate (%)
              </label>
              <div class="relative">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="employer-match"
                  value="50"
                  min="0"
                  max="200"
                  step="1"
                  class="text-input pr-5 font-mono text-sm"
                />
                <span
                  class="absolute right-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-sm"
                  >%</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
              <label
                for="employer-match-limit"
                class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal"
              >
                Employer Match Limit (% of salary)
              </label>
              <div class="relative">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="employer-match-limit"
                  value="6"
                  min="0"
                  max="50"
                  step="0.5"
                  class="text-input pr-5 font-mono text-sm"
                />
                <span
                  class="absolute right-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-sm"
                  >%</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Expected Return -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
            <label
              for="expected-return"
              class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal flex justify-between"
            >
              <span>Expected Annual Return</span>
              <span
                id="expected-return-val"
                class="font-mono text-stone font-bold">7.00%</span
              >
            </label>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <input
                type="range"
                id="expected-return-range"
                min="1"
                max="15"
                value="7"
                step="0.1"
                class="w-full cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
              />
              <div class="relative w-20 shrink-0">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="expected-return"
                  min="1"
                  max="15"
                  value="7"
                  step="0.05"
                  class="text-input pr-5 py-1 text-xs text-center font-mono h-8"
                />
                <span
                  class="absolute right-2 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-[10px]"
                  >%</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Collapsible Advanced Options Toggle -->
          <div class="border-t border-hairline pt-4 mt-2">
            <button
              type="button"
              id="advanced-toggle-btn"
              class="w-full flex items-center justify-between text-xs font-bold text-slate hover:text-primary transition-all cursor-pointer py-1"
            >
              <span class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                ⚙ Advanced Options (Inflation, Growth, Taxes & Limits)
              </span>
              <svg
                id="advanced-chevron"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="w-4 h-4 text-stone transition-transform duration-300"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2.5"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>

            <!-- Advanced Panel -->
            <div
              id="advanced-panel"
              class="max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 flex flex-col gap-4 border-t border-hairline-soft mt-3 pt-4"
            >
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
                  <label
                    for="inflation-rate"
                    class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-slate"
                  >
                    Annual Inflation Rate (%)
                  </label>
                  <div class="relative">
                    <input
                      type="number"
                      id="inflation-rate"
                      value="2.5"
                      min="0"
                      max="15"
                      step="0.1"
                      class="text-input pr-6 font-mono text-xs w-full"
                    />
                    <span
                      class="absolute right-2.5 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-xs"
                      >%</span
                    >
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
                  <label
                    for="salary-growth"
                    class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-slate"
                  >
                    Annual Salary Growth (%)
                  </label>
                  <div class="relative">
                    <input
                      type="number"
                      id="salary-growth"
                      value="3.0"
                      min="0"
                      max="15"
                      step="0.1"
                      class="text-input pr-6 font-mono text-xs w-full"
                    />
                    <span
                      class="absolute right-2.5 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-xs"
                      >%</span
                    >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Custom Currency overrides if custom selected -->
              <div
                id="custom-currency-container"
                class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 hidden border-t border-hairline-soft pt-2"
              >
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
                  <label
                    for="custom-currency-symbol"
                    class="text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate"
                    >Currency Symbol</label
                  >
                  <input
                    type="text"
                    id="custom-currency-symbol"
                    value="$"
                    class="text-input"
                  />
                </div>
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
                  <label
                    for="custom-currency-code"
                    class="text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate"
                    >Currency Code</label
                  >
                  <input
                    type="text"
                    id="custom-currency-code"
                    value="USD"
                    class="text-input"
                  />
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Account Type & Filing Status (Updates dynamically per country) -->
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
                  <label
